en_889362_0	Troops of the 57 Division under the Security Force Headquarters – Kilinochchi, (SFHQ-KLN), together with farming community in Ganeshapuram area on Saturday (30) launched a project to clean ‘Ganeshapuram’ water canal, fed by the main Iranamadu tank, running through a vast patch of paddy-fields in the area.
en_889362_1	On an initiative of Major General Vijitha Ravipriya, General Officer Commanding, 57 Division, around 50 troops of the 571 Brigade of the 57 Division under the SFHQ-KLN actively took part in the mammoth Shramadana campaign, together with a large gathering of farming community in the area who voluntarily joined hands with the troops.
en_889362_2	It was also a measure to further promote understanding and communal harmony between civilians and members of the Security Forces in the area.
en_889362_3	Major General Niyshshanka Ranawana, Commander, Security Forces- Kilinochchi (SF-KLN) has given his blessings to the project.
